{"recipe_desc": "I've combined several of the best techniques and tricks from our favorite chicken pot pie recipes to create a master recipe that, in my taste bud's opinion, surpasses them all. First, bake this in a large rectangular baking dish rather than a deep bowl. This will let you get crust with every bite. Second, pre-cook all of the vegetables so that they are crisp and don't get mushy when you add the roux. Third, add sherry to the roux sauce. This will add an amazing tang to the dish and plays an important chemical role in the oven so that the vegetable preserve their bright colors and flavors. A dash of Old Bay also brings out more of the chicken flavor and plays off of the other herbs and spices. Serve with a glass of wine and enjoy!", "recipe_category": ["Entrees"], "recipe_image": ["/recipes/chicken-pot-pie/chicken-pot-pie.jpg"], "recipe_total_time": ["PT1H30M"], "recipe_published_time": ["Mar 6, 2013"], "image_urls": ["http://www.makebetterfood.com/recipes/chicken-pot-pie/chicken-pot-pie.jpg"], "recipe_ingredients": ["1 \u00bd cups all-purpose flour", "\u00bd teaspoon salt", "\u00bd cup (1 stick) chilled unsalted butter, cut into six pieces", "\u00bc cup vegetable shortening", "3 to 4 tablespoons ice water", "4 carrots, thinly sliced", "4 celery stalks, thinly sliced", "4 small red or white potatoes, cubed", "1 \u00bd pounds boneless, skinless chicken breast", "2 cups low sodium chicken broth", "1 \u00bd tablespoons vegetable oil", "reserved vegetables", "4 tablespoons (\u00bd stick) unsalted butter", "\u00bd cup all purpose flour", "reserved chicken broth", "1 \u00bd cups milk", "\u00bd teaspoon dried thyme", "2 teaspoons salt, or to taste", "1 teaspoon Old Bay seasoning, or to taste", "\u00bd teaspoon pepper, or to taste", "3 tablespoons dry sherry (do not substitute or omit)", "\u00be cup green peas, frozen or fresh", "2-3 tablespoons minced fresh parsley"], "recipe_prep_time": ["PT1H"], "html": "<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n<title>Better Chicken Pot Pie Recipe - MakeBetterFood.com</title>\n<meta charset=\"utf-8\" />\n<meta http-equiv=\"Content-Type\" content=\"text/html;charset=utf-8\" />\n<link href=\"http://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Brawler\" rel=\"stylesheet\" type=\"text/css\" />\n<link href=\"/css/style.css\" rel=\"stylesheet\" type=\"text/css\" />\n<!--[if lte IE 7]>\n<link href=\"/css/ie7.css\" rel=\"stylesheet\" type=\"text/css\"/>\n<![endif]-->\n<link rel=\"shortcut icon\" href=\"/favicon.ico\" />\n<link rel=\"alternate\" type=\"application/rss+xml\" title=\"MakeBetterFood.com - Recipes, Learn How to Cook Amazing Food\" href=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/MakeBetterFood\"/>\n<meta property=\"og:title\" content=\"Better Chicken Pot Pie Recipe\"/>\n<meta property=\"og:type\" content=\"food\"/>\n<meta property=\"og:url\" content=\"http://www.makebetterfood.com/recipes/chicken-pot-pie/\"/>\n<meta property=\"og:image\" content=\"http://www.makebetterfood.com/recipes/chicken-pot-pie/chicken-pot-pie.jpg\"/>\n<meta property=\"og:site_name\" content=\"MakeBetterFood.com\"/>\n<meta property=\"og:description\" content=\"I've combined several of the best techniques and tricks from our favorite chicken pot pie recipes to create a master recipe that, in my taste bud's opinion, surpasses them all. First, bake this in a large rectangular baking dish rather than a deep bowl. This will let you get crust with every bite. Second, pre-cook all of the vegetables so that they are crisp and don't get mushy when you add the roux. Third, add sherry to the roux sauce. This will add an amazing tang to the dish and plays an important chemical role in the oven so that the vegetable preserve their bright colors and flavors. A dash of Old Bay also brings out more of the chicken flavor and plays off of the other herbs and spices. Serve with a glass of wine and enjoy!\"/>\n<meta property=\"fb:admins\" content=\"5711219\" />\n<!-- For Google Custom Site Search -->\n<!--\n<PageMap>\n<DataObject type=\"action\">\n