it for the chicken to cook, pre-measure the ingredients that you need for the roux and set aside.)", "Transfer the chicken to a large bowl, reserving the broth in a measuring cup.", "Increase the heat to medium-high and heat the oil in the now-empty pan. Add the carrots, celery, potatoes, and onions (if using) and saut\u00e9 until just tender, about five minutes.", "While the vegetables are saut\u00e9ing, shred the meat into bite-sized pieces. Transfer the cooked vegetables to the bowl with the chicken and set aside.", "Heat the butter over medium heat in the again-empty pan.", "When the foaming subsides, add flour and cook for about 1 minute.", "Whisk in reserved chicken broth, the milk, any accumulated chicken juices, and the thyme. Bring to a simmer and stir frequently with a whisk until the sauce fully thickens, about 10 additional minutes.", "Season with salt, pepper, and Old Bay to taste and stir in the sherry.", "Pour the sauce over the chicken and vegetable mixture and stir to combine.", "Stir in peas and parsley. Adjust seasonings as desired.", "Prepare ahead note: The mixture can be covered and refrigerated overnight. Reheat before topping with the pastry.", "Pour the mixture into a 13 by 9 inch baking pan or six 12-ounce ovenproof dishes. Roll out the dough and place on top of mixture, tucking in the sides.", "Bake until the pastry is golden brown and the filing is bubbling, about 30 minutes. Serve hot."], "images": [{"url": "http://www.makebetterfood.com/recipes/chicken-pot-pie/chicken-pot-pie.jpg", "path": "full/978673bdd9a338541ce80623a4aae23cca09c7fe.jpg", "checksum": "b891221cb08c131d1dac521cb8c8f2f9"}], "link": "http://www.makebetterfood.com/recipes/chicken-pot-pie/", "recipe_cook_time": ["PT30M"], "recipe_yield": ["Serves 8"]}